    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix QoS flow parameter handling in F1AP DU side processing\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP DU side was not properly extracting QoS flow parameters from incoming F1AP messages, causing a configuration mismatch between protocol layers. This led to inconsistent behavior downstream where QoS information was expected but not available.\n\nThe issue was that while the CU side was correctly setting QoS parameters in F1AP messages, the DU side was completely ignoring the QoSInformation IE and not storing these parameters in the UE context.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added `f1ap_drb_qos_info_t` structure and integrated it into `f1ap_drb_to_be_setup_t`\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_ue_context_management.c`: Added QoS parameter extraction logic in UE context setup and modification handlers\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_cu_ue_context_management.c`: Added initialization consistency for QoS info structures\n\n"
}